<section class="pt-24 pb-12">
  <h1
    class="
      text-[clamp(34px,5vw,52px)] leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.028em] font-semibold m-0
      mb-8 text-balance max-w-[680px] text-sage-12
    "
  >
    Andrew Mason<span class="text-mint-11">.</span>
  </h1>
  <p
    class="
      text-[16.5px] text-sage-11 max-w-[600px] leading-[1.65] m-0 mb-4 text-pretty
    "
  >
    Ruby on Rails engineer at
    <%= render Link.new(href: "https://podia.com", variant: :inline) do %>Podia<% end %>, co-host of
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/speaking/", variant: :inline) do %>Remote Ruby<% end %>, and based in Arizona.
  </p>
  <p
    class="
      text-[16.5px] text-sage-11 max-w-[600px] leading-[1.65] m-0 mb-4 text-pretty
    "
  >
    I write about Rails, Ruby tooling, and the stuff I learn while shipping
    software for a living. Most posts started as a note I was writing for
    myself and turned out to be useful for somebody else.
  </p>
  <p
    class="
      text-[16.5px] text-sage-11 max-w-[600px] leading-[1.65] m-0 mb-4 text-pretty
    "
  >
    You'll find my
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/posts/", variant: :inline) do %>writing<% end %>,
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/projects/", variant: :inline) do %>open source<% end %>, and
    <%= render Link.new(href: "/speaking/", variant: :inline) do %>talks and podcasts<% end %>
    here. Mostly so I can find them again later.
  </p>
  <%= render Link.new(href: "/posts/", variant: :action) do %>
    Read the writing
    <%= render Icon.new(
      name: "arrow_right",
      class: "transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1",
    ) %>
  <% end %>
</section>
